The Bony King Of Nowhere

by Luke A. Jones

You are in Your Hovel.

You can see a Battered Wooden Chest and Your Dog.

You can go out.

You are in your hovel in the northernmost borderlands of the Kingdom of Nowhere.

It is a round wattle and daub hut. There is a fireplace in the middle with a hole in the thatch roof above it acting as a chimney.

Around the circumference of the room there are a few sticks of furniture and rags that represent the totality of your worldly possessions.

(type 'hints' for game specific help at anytime)

> x me

> x me

You are thin and your skin is grimy, you are wearing grey ragged woollen clothing
> i

> i

You are not carrying anything.
> x dog

> x dog

It's your faithful canine companion, he's an ageing Boxer mongrel of some sort, he has tan brown fur with a white patch on his chest. He's seen a few too many scrapes and doesn't smell too sweet, but you love him dearly and he's called Dylan.
> pet dog

> pet dog

Dylan nuzzles against your leg and looks up to you with doleful eyes, his tail wagging expectantly. Some of his mooting hair collects in your hand, you shove it in your pocket
> x hair

> x hair

A few strands of Dylan's brown and white hair
> x furniture

> x furniture

Furniture might be a rather grand term what consists of a filthy straw bed and a battered wooden chest
> x bed

> x bed

Several large rectangular bales of hay lashed together, it is blackened with grime and splattered with mud
> x chest

> x chest

An ancient wooden chest that has been repeatedly patched and repaired. You'll be pleased to know there is no lock.
> open it

> open it

You open it.
It contains an axe.
> x axe

> x axe

An axe with an arms length wooden haft and a steel head with the letter L and the pattern of a rose embossed on it. It is your prized (and only) possession given to you by your father. It's blade is a sharp as Jack after a busy day.
> take it

> take it

You pick it up.
> x fireplace

> x fireplace

A round circle of flat stones with the ashen remains of last night's fire smouldering in the middle. Leaning against the fireplace is a shovel.
> x stone

> x stone

A circle of flat whetstones bearing heavy scratch marks.
> x shovel

> x shovel

A small wooden shovel that you use for removing ashes. It's a ground-breaking design.
> take it

> take it

You pick it up.
> sharpen axe

> sharpen axe

You walk over to the hearthstones and sharpen the axe blade on one of them. After a minute or so it gleams with a wicked edge, it's now an axis of evil.

> x rags

> x rags

A pile of rags that were once clothes, now too threadbare to wear
> take rags

> take rags

You pick them up.
> out

> out

You are in the Northern Meadow.

You can see Your Dog.

You can go in or south.

You are in the meadow outside your hovel, several acres of wild grassland and wild flowers. You may be dirt poor, but the beauty of the landscape is some consolation.

As you step out of your home there is a beating of wings above your head, looking up you see a pigeon rapidly disappearing out of sight, and a letter flutters to your feet, you pick it up.

 On the wind you can hear a distant shout of what sounds like "Fuck yooouuuu..." coming from the pigeon's direction before it disappears from sight.

> x letter

> x letter

The letter is addressed to the Bony King of Nowhere, at his palace in the capital Lost, many miles to the south.

On the reverse is written;

"If found please deliver personally to the King, the contents are confidential and you are forbidden from reading them. Failure to comply with either of these requests will result in summary execution."

Well that's just perfect you think, you've always hated a) the capital, b) the monarchy, and c) the south in general.
