You are at Coley's Mill.

You can see a Hand Water Pump and Your Dog.

You can go west, in or north.

You are stood in the yard of Coley's Mill, towering above you is the windmill, it is painted bright red. There is a stiff breeze today but the sails are motionless.

> x pump

> x pump

A green hand pump fixed over a well, there is a large lever on the side of it.
> x windmill

> x windmill

The bright red windmill towers above you, it has four large slated wooden sails which are stationary even though there is a stiff breeze.
> in

> in

You are in The Windmill.

You can see a Wooden Table, Wendy Miller, some Stairs and Your Dog.

You can go out or up.

You are inside the windmill, in the middle of the room are the enormous grinding stones with a huge wooden axle leading up into the ceiling.

Also in the room is a wooden table, at which sits Wendy the Miller, fast asleep and snoring like a congested hippo.

> x Wendy

> x Wendy

A stern looking dark haired lady, she is wearing a pale blue shin length smock, a red neckerchief, and a brown Quaker style hat. She is currently sound asleep and snoring at an unbelievable volume. A fog of cider fumes is in the air around her.
> x table

> x table

It's a plain wooden table made from pine, on top of the table is Wendy's slumped head and an empty jug of cider
> x jug

> x jug

An empty quart sized jug of cider. Written on the label it says 'Dicken's Cider, 8.5%, please drink responsibly.'
> take jug

> take jug

You pick it up.
> x stairs

> x stairs

Wooden stairs leading up to the top floor of the Windmill, you can see a mouse, there, there on the stairs, right there.
> x mouse

> x mouse

A tiny grey-furred mouse, who looks to all the world as if it's wearing tiny little clogs, it's making a 'clip-clippety clop' noise as it scurries up and down the stairs.
> u

> u

You are in The Top floor of Windmill.

You can see a Mousetrap and Your Dog.

You can go down.

You are inside the top floor of the windmill, the dome roof curves above you, and on one wall you can see the stationary horizontal sail shaft where it enters and connects via a gear to the vertical shaft leading straight down to the grinding room below.

> x mousetrap

> x mousetrap

A wooden spring loaded mouse trap, with a piece of cheese as bait. You consider these traps rather cruel, so you decide to caerphilly unset the trap and place the piece of cheese in your pocket.
> x cheese

> x cheese

A small piece of cheese that you stole from a mousetrap, it's not your cheese, in fact it's Nacho Cheese.
> d

> d

You are in The Windmill.

You can see a Wooden Table, Wendy Miller, some Stairs and Your Dog.

You can go out or up.

You are inside the windmill, in the middle of the room are the enormous grinding stones with a huge wooden axle leading up into the ceiling.

Also in the room is a wooden table, at which sits Wendy the Miller, fast asleep and snoring like a congested hippo.

> give cheese to mouse

> give cheese to mouse

You break a small piece off the lump of cheese and give it to the mouse. The mouse reaches up with it's little front paws, grabs the cheese, gobbles it down, then gives a tiny squeak of appreciation.

Somewhere from the folds of its fur it produces a tiny business card and holds it up to you, you take it. The mouse scurries off out of sight.
> x card

> x card

A tiny business card, made of exquisite silken paper. In a minute gothic script it reads,

_______________________________________________________________________

'Gerald T. Mouse, freelance adventurer, no quest too great or small.'

'Payment in cheese only!'

________________________________________________________________
