You are at Coley's Mill.

You can see a Hand Water Pump and Your Dog.

You can go west, in or north.

You are stood in the yard of Coley's Mill, towering above you is the windmill, it is painted bright red. There is a stiff breeze today but the sails are motionless.

> fill jug

> fill jug

You place the jug under the spout of the pump and crank the lever, with three pumps the jug is full of freezing cold water, you pick it up
> in

> in

You are in The Windmill.

You can see a Wooden Table, Wendy Miller, some Stairs and Your Dog.

You can go out or up.

You are inside the windmill, in the middle of the room are the enormous grinding stones with a huge wooden axle leading up into the ceiling.

Also in the room is a wooden table, at which sits Wendy the Miller, fast asleep and snoring like a congested hippo.

> pour water on Wendy

> pour water on Wendy

With some trepidation you empty the jug of freezing cold water over the Miller's head. With a jolt she wakes up, shrieks and jumps out of her chair. Just as she is about to start shouting at you Dylan bounds over to her, wagging his tail and looking at her with his doleful eyes, "What the hell..I..er...Oh! Aren't you an adorable little pooch! Aren't you? Aren't you? Who's a lovely pooch?"

The Miller looks up at you and says, "Er, bit of a late night on the cider, please don't tell anyone, what I can I do for you?"
> ask Wendy about windmill

> ask Wendy about windmill

"Fabulous contraption isn't it? There's rumours from Lost of a new technology coming to replace 'em, something to do with fire and steam, sounds hideous."
> ask Wendy about mouse

> ask Wendy about mouse

"That damn creature, clip-clippety-clopping all over the place, does me head in!"
> ask Wendy about axe

> ask Wendy about axe

"Only two things in life are certain: death and axes. The former usually follows the latter."
