You are at The Desolate Beach.

You can see a Bottle, The Sea of Emptiness and Your Dog.

You can go south.

You are on long, bleak, sandy beach on the shore of the Sea of Emptiness. There is a brisk and bracing (i.e. bloody freezing) sea-breeze.

 Dylan bounds around in circles in the sand wagging his tail.

> take bottle

> take bottle

You pick it up.
> x it

> x it

A blue glass bottle with the word "FLY" embossed on it.
> open bottle

> open bottle

You open it.
It contains a Scroll of paper.
> take scroll

> take scroll

You pick it up.
> x scroll

> x scroll

You unfurl the scroll of paper it reads,

"Help! We're under siege, the Bony King has been imprisoned in his Castle. General D'sarray and the armed forces have assumed control"

You let out an audible groan and say to yourself. 'let me get this straight, if I don't deliver the letter then the King will have me killed, if on the otherhand I do try to deliver it then the General will have me killed.'

You turn the scroll over and on the reverse side there is a printed score of music, titled "Adagio in G Minor, by Albinoni", you vaguely remember the piece from the piano lessons your father gave you, back in more comfortable times.
> x sea

> x sea

The sea stretches as far as the horizon. A powerful surf is roaring and rolling before pounding into the shore, then receding for a few seconds and crashing in again.
> dig

> dig

You dig in the sand and find a small smooth glass sphere, you pick it up.
> x sphere

> x sphere

A fist sized glass sphere, it is perfectly smooth and round, but has a smeared and dirty surface.
> clean sphere

> clean sphere

Using the rags from your home you polish the surface of he sphere until it shines and reflects an inverted curved image of your face.
> x sphere

> x sphere

A fist sized glass sphere, it is perfectly smooth and round, it has a highly polished surface. It reflects a curved and inverted image of the landscape.
