You are on long, bleak, sandy beach on the shore of the Sea of Emptiness. There is a brisk and bracing (i.e. bloody freezing) sea-breeze.

 Dylan bounds around in circles in the sand wagging his tail.

> fish

> fish

You cast your rod and the spinner flies above the crashing waves, lands with a splash and sinks out of sight, pulling the line behind it.

You hold the rod tightly and wait, the surf is pulling strongly on the line.

You wait...and wait...and wait..Dylan digs around in the sand impatiently...and you wait..and the suddenly there is tremendous pull on the line and you struggle to hold on to the rod.

Pulling back on the rod you heave a large struggling Copper Fish on to the bank. You dispatch it with a clean blow and pick it up.
